Vice President Kamala Harris held a meeting with White House Counsel Dana Remus to discuss the importance of ensuring easy and accessible voting opportunities for all Americans. She expressed her admiration for poll workers and their commitment to upholding democracy, but also highlighted the threats and intimidation they faced during the 2020 election. Harris emphasized the need to protect the right to vote and discussed the administration's efforts to increase voter access, stop anti-voter legislation, and pass voting rights acts. The meeting concluded with Harris expressing gratitude to the participants for their work and patriotism. Press Secretary Jen Psaki also commented on Speaker Pelosi's decision to reject Representatives Banks and Jordan from the January 6 Commission, stating the importance of a thorough and transparent investigation into the events of that day.